==English==

===Noun===
'''[[prise]] de [[fer]]''' (From French, literally ''take the steel'')
# {{fencing}} an [[engagement]] of the [[blade]]s that attempts to control the opponent's [[weapon]]


A preperation of attack in which the partner's blade is taken by envelopment, a bind or a croise. A pris-de-fer can only be effective when the partner's arm is extended with blade in line, as without suitable resistance the latter cannot be controlled and transported to a new poistion by the dominating opposition of forte to foible.
-From the Actor Combatant Glossary of Terms Revised 2001